title._content: Petition in the Case of U.S. ex. rel. John Wheeler v. Passmore Williamson, 07/18/1855

description._content: Title: Petition in the Case of U.S. ex. rel. John Wheeler v. Passmore Williamson, 07/18/1855 From: Record Group/Collection: 21 Record Hierarchy Level: Item Scope and Content Note: John H. Wheeler's petition stated that he owns three persons named Jane, Daniel and Isaiah who were removed by Passmore Williamson and asks the Court to command Williamson to return these persons. Reference Unit: National Archives at Philadelphia Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=2641489 Repository Contact Information: NARA’s Mid Atlantic Region (Philadelphia) (NRBA), 900 Market Street, Philadelphia, PA, 19107-4292..
